data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['hæri]
*ngoại động từ
 ■phiền nhiễu, làm phiền, quấy rầy
 ■cướp bóc, tàn phá

Anh - Anh
harry
■ verb (harries, harrying, harried)
1》 persistently carry out attacks on (an enemy).
2》 persistently harass.
Origin
OE herian, hergian, of Gmc origin.

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
harry
▸ verb
1they harried the retreating enemy: ATTACK, assail, assault; charge, rush, strike, set upon; bombard, shell, strafe.
2the government was harried by a new lobby: HARASS, hound, pressurize, bedevil, torment, pester, bother, worry, badger, nag, plague; informal hassle, bug, lean on, give someone a hard time, get on someone's back.
